<div class="wrapper padded">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">Thanks for taking the demo!</h1>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">
        <div class="row">
          <h3 class="text-center">So, here's what we asked you and the answers you gave:</h3>
          <div class="slightly-padded">
            <div class="card col-xs-12 col-md-4">
              <div class="text-center card-bg-gradient">
                <h4>Q1: <%= Question.find(@the_questions[0].id).content  %></h4>
                <p><%= Answer.find_by(question_id: @the_questions[0].id).content %></p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card col-xs-12 col-md-4">
              <div class="text-center card-bg-gradient">
                <h4>Q1: <%= Question.find(@the_questions[1].id).content  %></h4>
                <p><%= Answer.find_by(question_id: @the_questions[1].id).content %></p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card col-xs-12 col-md-4">
              <div class="text-center card-bg-gradient">
                <h4>Q1: <%= Question.find(@the_questions[2].id).content  %></h4>
                <p><%= Answer.find_by(question_id: @the_questions[2].id).content %></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper light-bg padded">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
        <div class="card-big">
          <h3>Here's our analysis of your positivity levels based on your first response:</h3>
          <div class="card-square" style="background-image: linear-gradient(-225deg, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 0%, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 50%);">
            <h3>Put a graph here (bar chart, maybe?)</h3>
            <%= javascript_include_tag "//code.highcharts.com/highcharts.js", "chartkick" %>
            <%= column_chart [["Positivity", @the_questions[0].answer.pos]] %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
        <div class="card-big">
          <h3>And here are the collective results of everyone who's taken the demo so far:</h3>
          <div class="card-square" style="background-image: linear-gradient(-225deg, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 0%, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 50%);">
            <h3>Put the line graph here</h3>
            <%= line_chart ConversationHistory.where(user_id: 1).select {|user_conversation| !user_conversation.answers.average(:pos).nil?}.map {|user_conversation| [user_conversation.created_at, user_conversation.answers.average(:pos)]} %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper padded">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-10 col md offset-1">
        <h2>How would this work for your team?</h2>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
            <p>After one of your team members answers the questions, the results will be available for you to see on your profile page.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">
            <div class="card-square" style="background-image: linear-gradient(-225deg, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 0%, rgba(45,125,92,0.6) 50%);"><h3>screenshot of the profile link in the navbar</h3></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

